  <!-- Slide 5: Fintech Disruptors -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Fintech Disruption</h2>
    <div class="row gap-lg fill-height">
      <div class="fill-width" style="background-color: #1e293b; padding: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 class="mb-4" style="color: #38bdf8;">Figure Technologies</h3>
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1; font-size: 0.95rem;">Nation's largest nonbank HELOC originator. $12.5B funded via blockchain. 5-minute approvals, 5-day funding. 30%+ EBITDA margins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fill-width" style="background-color: #1e293b; padding: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 class="mb-4" style="color: #38bdf8;">Spring EQ</h3>
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1; font-size: 0.95rem;">Digital-native HELOC platform. Data-driven underwriting, remote verification. Rapid customer acquisition.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fill-width" style="background-color: #1e293b; padding: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 class="mb-4" style="color: #38bdf8;">Rocket Mortgage</h3>
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1; font-size: 0.95rem;">Chase partnership for HELOCs. Combines digital excellence with bank distribution power.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 6: How Mortgage Business Works -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Mortgage Business Model</h2>
    <div class="fill-height">
      <ul class="text-lg" style="color: #cbd5e1;">
        <li><strong>Origination:</strong> Lender evaluates borrower, approves loan, earns origination fees (0.5-1% of loan)</li>
        <li><strong>Servicing:</strong> Lender collects payments, manages escrow, earns servicing fees (0.25-0.50% annually)</li>
        <li><strong>Secondary Market:</strong> Loans sold to investors/GSEs for liquidity; lender retains servicing rights</li>
        <li><strong>Revenue Streams:</strong> Origination fees, servicing fees, interest income, gain-on-sale margins</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 7: Mortgage Funding Process -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">How Mortgages Get Funded</h2>
    <div class="row gap-lg fill-height">
      <div class="fill-width" style="background-color: #1e293b; padding: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 class="mb-4" style="color: #38bdf8;">1. Origination Capital</h3>
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1;">Banks use deposits, credit lines, warehouse facilities to fund loans at closing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fill-width" style="background-color: #1e293b; padding: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 class="mb-4" style="color: #38bdf8;">2. Portfolio vs Sale</h3>
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1;">Keep loans (portfolio) for interest income OR sell to secondary market for liquidity.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fill-width" style="background-color: #1e293b; padding: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 class="mb-4" style="color: #38bdf8;">3. Capital Recycling</h3>
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1;">Sale proceeds fund new originations, creating continuous lending capacity.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 8: Secondary Market Process -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Secondary Market Mechanics</h2>
    <div class="fill-height">
      <ul class="text-lg" style="color: #cbd5e1;">
        <li><strong>GSE Purchase:</strong> Fannie Mae/Freddie Mac buy conforming loans, bundle into MBS for investors</li>
        <li><strong>Servicing Rights:</strong> Originating lender retains servicing, collects payments, earns ongoing fees</li>
        <li><strong>Investor Returns:</strong> MBS investors receive principal and interest payments from borrowers</li>
        <li><strong>Liquidity Creation:</strong> System converts illiquid mortgages into tradable securities, enabling scale</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 9: Mortgage Loan Categories Part 1 -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Mortgage Categories (Part 1)</h2>
    <div class="fill-height">
      <ul class="text-lg" style="color: #cbd5e1;">
        <li><strong>Conforming Loans:</strong> Meet FHFA standards, backed by Fannie/Freddie, limits $806,500 (2026 most areas)</li>
        <li><strong>Non-Conforming:</strong> Exceed limits or don't meet GSE standards, higher risk, retained or private sale</li>
        <li><strong>Jumbo Loans:</strong> Exceed conforming limits, strong credit required, portfolio or private securitization</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 10: Mortgage Loan Categories Part 2 -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Mortgage Categories (Part 2)</h2>
    <div class="fill-height">
      <ul class="text-lg" style="color: #cbd5e1;">
        <li><strong>FHA Loans:</strong> Insured by FHA, 3.5% down (580 credit), accessible for first-time buyers, mortgage insurance required</li>
        <li><strong>VA Loans:</strong> Guaranteed by VA for veterans, 0% down, no mortgage insurance, competitive rates</li>
        <li><strong>USDA Loans:</strong> Rural property financing, 0% down for eligible areas, income restrictions apply</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 11: Entry Strategy Part 1 -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Best Entry Strategies (Part 1)</h2>
    <div class="fill-height">
      <ul class="text-lg" style="color: #cbd5e1;">
        <li><strong>Leverage Existing Customer Base:</strong> Cross-sell HELOCs to 68M Wells Fargo customers with mortgage/deposit relationships</li>
        <li><strong>Digital-First Origination:</strong> Deploy AI-powered underwriting, 5-minute approvals, automated document verification</li>
        <li><strong>Competitive Pricing:</strong> Use low-cost deposit funding advantage vs fintech, transparent rate structure</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 12: Entry Strategy Part 2 -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Best Entry Strategies (Part 2)</h2>
    <div class="fill-height">
      <ul class="text-lg" style="color: #cbd5e1;">
        <li><strong>Mobile-First Experience:</strong> Seamless mobile application, real-time status tracking, e-signature closing</li>
        <li><strong>Product Innovation:</strong> Hybrid fixed/variable HELOCs, rate lock options, flexible draw structures for diverse needs</li>
        <li><strong>Regional Focus:</strong> Target high-equity, high-affordability markets where inventory constraints are lower</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 13: Technology Imperatives -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Technology Requirements</h2>
    <div class="fill-height">
      <ul class="text-lg" style="color: #cbd5e1;">
        <li><strong>Modern LOS:</strong> End-to-end loan origination system with HELOC-specific workflows, API integrations</li>
        <li><strong>AI/ML Underwriting:</strong> Automated credit assessment, fraud detection, risk scoring for rapid decisioning</li>
        <li><strong>CRM Integration:</strong> Unified customer view, lead management, automated marketing for cross-sell opportunities</li>
        <li><strong>Compliance Automation:</strong> Fair lending monitoring, algorithmic bias detection, regulatory reporting</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 14: Regulatory Landscape -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">2026 Regulatory Environment</h2>
    <div class="fill-height">
      <ul class="text-lg" style="color: #cbd5e1;">
        <li><strong>Enhanced Fair Lending:</strong> Algorithmic bias scrutiny, standardized assessment methodologies, expanded reporting</li>
        <li><strong>Digital Certifications:</strong> Specialized licensing for digital mortgage operations, cybersecurity mandates</li>
        <li><strong>Transparency Requirements:</strong> Clear disclosure of lending criteria, decision rationales for declined applications</li>
        <li><strong>ESG Considerations:</strong> Environmental risk assessment, climate impact disclosure on property values</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 15: Competitive Advantages -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Wells Fargo Competitive Moats</h2>
    <div class="row gap-lg fill-height">
      <div class="fill-width" style="background-color: #1e293b; padding: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 class="mb-4" style="color: #38bdf8;">Scale</h3>
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1;">68M retail customers, existing mortgage relationships, deep deposit base for low-cost funding.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fill-width" style="background-color: #1e293b; padding: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 class="mb-4" style="color: #38bdf8;">Brand Trust</h3>
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1;">Established financial services brand with branch network for hybrid digital-physical experience.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fill-width" style="background-color: #1e293b; padding: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 class="mb-4" style="color: #38bdf8;">Data</h3>
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1;">Rich customer financial data enables predictive analytics, personalized offers, superior risk assessment.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 16: Risk Mitigation -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Risk Management Framework</h2>
    <div class="fill-height">
      <ul class="text-lg" style="color: #cbd5e1;">
        <li><strong>Credit Risk:</strong> Conservative LTV caps (70-80%), rigorous income verification, debt-to-income limits</li>
        <li><strong>Interest Rate Risk:</strong> Balanced portfolio of fixed/variable products, hedging strategies, stress testing</li>
        <li><strong>Operational Risk:</strong> Robust fraud detection, secure digital infrastructure, compliance monitoring</li>
        <li><strong>Reputational Risk:</strong> Transparent pricing, fair lending practices, superior customer service standards</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 17: Financial Projections -->
  <section class="slide p-16 col" style="background-color: #0f172a; color: #f1f5f9;">
    <h2 class="mb-6" style="color: #38bdf8;">Business Case</h2>
    <div class="fill-height">
      <ul class="text-lg" style="color: #cbd5e1;">
        <li><strong>Revenue Opportunity:</strong> 15-17% market share of $228.25B market = $34-39B addressable by 2031</li>
        <li><strong>Margin Profile:</strong> Origination fees 0.5-1%, servicing fees 0.25-0.5%, net interest margin 2-3%</li>
        <li><strong>Growth Trajectory:</strong> 4.12% market CAGR + share gain from fintech = 6-8% revenue growth potential</li>
        <li><strong>Efficiency Target:</strong> Digital automation reduces cost per loan 30-40%, targeting sub-$500 origination cost</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
